Vision Trip Description
67	Vision Trip Description	We offer a program each summer called Launch Intensive that provides potential teachers an opportunity to see the city, school, and culture by participating in a 12 day trip to North Africa. On this trip, prospective teachers live with a local family connected to our school and attend language and culture classes. It gives them a chance to get a glimpse of life overseas, as well as see our school and how it functions in an international context.
Security
90	Security Explanation	Our school seeks to engage the unreached through education. Most of our students are North African who come from Muslim backgrounds and have had little to no engagement with Christians. In our classrooms, we use a Christian worldview to inform instruction and form deep relationships with our students and their families. It is through these relationships that the gospel is shared through our example and the conversations we have over coffee and tea. Because of the resistance to foreign ideas (including religion), we have to be mindful when sharing our faith and talking about the purpose of our school.
